description._content: Description: Group of natural reproduction of Troodos Pine trees - Pinus nigra var. Karamanica in front and between mature trees, Age about 250 years, Troodos Forest, Elevation 5,760 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Mother trees of Troodos Pine - Pinus nigra var. Karmanica, with self-sown seedlings, 13th March, 1930. Troodos Forest, Elevation 5,700 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 13 March 1930 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
